==Abstract==

This IIP describes a P2P protocol for light clients to download compact block filters and use them to determine block relevance. It is adapted from BIP 157 for INTcoin.

==Motivation==

Light clients need to identify blocks containing their transactions. Bloom filters (IIP-11) leak privacy. Compact block filters:

* Are computed once per block by full nodes
* Allow clients to match locally without revealing addresses
* Provide better privacy guarantees

==Specification==

===Messages===

'''getcfilters''': Request filters
<pre>
filter_type:  uint8    // Filter type (0 = basic)
start_height: uint32   // Starting block height
stop_hash:    uint256  // Ending block hash
</pre>

'''cfilter''': Filter response
<pre>
filter_type:  uint8
block_hash:   uint256
filter:       []byte   // Golomb-Rice encoded filter
</pre>

'''getcfheaders''': Request filter headers
<pre>
filter_type:  uint8
start_height: uint32
stop_hash:    uint256
</pre>

'''cfheaders''': Filter headers response
<pre>
filter_type:    uint8
stop_hash:      uint256
previous_header: uint256
filter_hashes:  []uint256
</pre>

'''getcfcheckpt''': Request filter checkpoints
<pre>
filter_type: uint8
stop_hash:   uint256
</pre>

'''cfcheckpt''': Filter checkpoints response
<pre>
filter_type:   uint8
stop_hash:     uint256
filter_headers: []uint256  // Every 1000 blocks
</pre>

===Filter Header Chain===

Filter headers form a commitment chain:
<pre>
filter_header[0] = SHA3-256(filter[0] || 0x00...00)
filter_header[n] = SHA3-256(filter[n] || filter_header[n-1])
</pre>

===INTcoin Adaptation===

* Uses SHA3-256 instead of double-SHA256 for filter headers

